55.1	Widget_engine	Software widget	Desktop widgets (commonly just called widgets) are interactive virtual tools that provide single-purpose services such as showing the user the latest news, the current weather, the time, a calendar, a dictionary, a map program, a calculator, desktop notes, photo viewers, or even a language translator, among other things. Examples of widget engines include:	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e4/Wikiwidget.png/220px-Wikiwidget.png
